name: Boom City Fireworks COVID Vaccine Site
info:
*************THIS IS A PFIZER CLINIC********** 

Everyone 12 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination. 

Please also note that, even if you are otherwise eligible, you must be 18 or older for the Moderna or Johnson & Johnson vaccine, and 12 or older for the Pfizer vaccine (parent/guardian must be present to sign the consent form). 

Appointments are highly recommended but not required. Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves. 

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Walla Walla County HD- COVID Provider
address: Walla Walla County Fairgrounds, Walla Walla WA, 99362
info:
**THIS CLINIC IS BY APPOINTMENT ONLY FOR 1st DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS for all qualifying individuals aged 12 years & over at the Walla Walla Fairgrounds. Parental/Guardian consent is required for 12 – 17 year olds, parent/guardian consent and signature can be completed on-site or in the final screen of the online registration process.
Given the limited supply of COVID-19 vaccine available at this time and Washington's commitment to equitable and fair access, those seeking COVID-19 vaccines at this clinic location you must either live or work, or get your medical care in Washington state.  Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided. **Enter the fairgrounds from Orchard Street into Gate 5.**
We look forward to seeing you. Thanks for keeping Walla Walla well.
** ESTA CLÍNICA ES CON CITA SOLAMENTE PARA LAS VACUNAS DE LA PRIMERA DOSIS DE PFIZER para personas calificadas de 12 años en Adelante en el recinto ferial del condado de Walla Walla.  Se requiere el consentimiento de los padres / tutores para los jóvenes de 12 - 17 años, las firmas y el consentimiento en la pantalla de registro final.** 

Dado el suministro limitado de la vacuna COVID-19 disponible en este momento y el compromiso de Washington con el acceso equitativo y justo, aquellos que buscan vacunas para el COVID-19 en esta clínica deben vivir o trabajar, o recibir atención médica en el estado de Washington.  El cubre bocas es requerido. Si no tiene un cubre bocas, se le proporcionará una. ** Entre los terrenos de la feria por la calle Orchard Street hasta la entrada 5. ** Esperamos verlo. Gracias por cuidar a Walla Walla.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Skamakawa Resort Clinic
info: ****This is a JOHNSON & JOHNSON single dose vaccine clinic. **** and is by appointment or walk in.  Please note: Johnson & Johnson vaccine can only be administered to individuals 18 years of age or older according CDC requirements.  This clinic is located at and hosted by Skamokawa Resort in partnership with Wahkiakum Health and Human Services, WA Department of Health and WA National Guard. This is a walk-in location. Please let us know if you or someone you are accompanying needs assistance of any kind. **You should also plan your visit around waiting for 15 minutes in the observation area so we can monitor for any unlikely adverse reactions to the vaccine.** Certain people with pre-identified conditions or past anaphylaxis events may be asked to wait for 30 minutes of observation. Free language translation services are provided. Video ASL translation is also provided. Please do not come if you are feeling ill.  It is best to wear clothes that will allow for access to your upper arm, just below the shoulder. **Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
